tip.text: Located in the town, about $200/night with heating but no aircon, just a fan that seems good enough for late June travel. Nice, clean & spacious rooms with comfy beds & washroom. Free parking & wifi.
Nice place to relax, swim and do fly fishing.
The bridge is closed for reconstruction and will be open in Fall 2017.
Nice place to fish and to buy fresh trouts. The young chap even helped us to clean the fish! Only the locals will know this place!

venue.name: Bethel Woods Center for the Arts
Bethel Woods Center for the Arts
Bethel Woods Center for the Arts

tip.text: My fav place for authentic Chinese noodles as I love their Fish meat spicy noodles. Lanzhou noodles is good & not spicy. Might be bland for some. I like to order herbal drink to go with the noodles!
My fav spot for Cambodian noodles. It tastes exactly like Teochew noodles that I've eaten in Singapore therefore always going back for it. Good service with generous servings & reasonably priced.

formattedAddress: 216 Grand St (btwn Mott and Elizabeth St)

venue.name: Grand Bo Ky Restaurant 波記潮州小食

tip.text: I like their "salty" chicken, pork ribs tim sum, salted fish minced pork over rice, beef porridge, sandwiches and ginger lemon drink. Yet to discover the rest on the menu.
Came here bcos Visual Arts Optics (SG) broke my spectacles & were rude. Many choices here with good service & reasonable pricing. I've been wearing the specs made at OOPPA for 10days, so far so good!

Went on 17/2 to pickup my spects. 3days later nosepad broke & the guy was rude & unhelpful. Not sure if they strained the nosepad while replacing the lenses. Utterly disappointed. Can't wear at all =(
Service is quite good. The queue is sometimes short but today is very long and the estimated waiting time of 30mins is very misleading as the wait is about 1.5hrs...😞
Ngon serves noodles and rice. Their spring rolls and lemongrass drink are good. Beef noodles is ok. Staff are friendly.

Hawker Chan Hong Kong Soya Sauce Chicken Rice & Noodle

tip.text: Was here on 23/1, short queue. Cha siew is nice, chicken not as tender, pork belly fatty, wonton soup has a funny taste, roselle drink tastes like medicine, noodles are ok, don't fancy their chilli.

Mei Xiang Black & White Fish Soup

tip.text: Clean & nice room, lovely old building with an unusually old elevator. Did not try the breakfast or cheese but the hot drinks 24/7 is good. The lift broke down when we checked out which is not good.
Pho & chicken wings are very tasty & authentic! Very reasonably priced with helpful staff! Small place but worth trying! Will love to go there again as I was missing their food the next morning!

Surprised that the pho & crepe are so good & reasonably priced! Nice staff, small place with decent space. Not easy to find the cafe as you can only see their house number 2841 (not name) from outside

formattedAddress: 2841 W Sunset Blvd (at Silver Lake Blvd.)

tip.text: Nice staff though the food is not authentic. Miso soup is blend but okay. Soba was not used for soba dish while gyoza does not have the right taste. I'm just too used to the taste from Japan.
Pho Tai and Pho Bo Hue are good! If you are not a very big eater, the small bowl should be more than enough as their portion is generous. Authentic and delicious Vietnamese food!
Come with an empty stomach to this nice and big market where you can find a good selection of food, drinks and local products. A place you should not miss in San Francisco!
You'll love their lobsters and other fresh seafood! Price has increased by almost 50% in about 3 years!
Delicious food with generous serving & very reasonably priced. Salmon rice, Beef rice & chicken wings are must try! Been there twice. Will be back again!

formattedAddress: 28 Watts St (btwn Thompson St and 6th Ave)

tip.text: Clean hotel with helpful staff (reception, cafe, housekeeping etc), small rooms (lousy curtain design), free wifi & breakfast. Good location which makes moving around convenient & finding food easy.

Authentic Pho Xe Lua as the soup is the best among other restaurants in NY. Just that there is only 1 slice of tendon, 1 beef ball with few slices of raw beef, brisket, etc. Tasty homemade ginger tea.
Tasty Beef Flank Pho and Fishcake Bowl!
Flavorful Indian food. I like their mutton, papaddam, dosai, teh tarik, etc. Missing the days when I was in India.
Prawn pasta is good. Tuna is fine but not to my liking. Staff are polite. Why did the waitress not ask for the doneness of the ribeye? Place is hot (no aircon) & noisy. Not a place I will go again
Tasty San Lou Bee Hoon, Flower clams, Salted egg prawn balls, Pepper crab & Bittergourd Pork Ribs! Reasonably priced though the place might not seem to be very clean or nice.
Tasty San Lou Bee Hoon, Flower clams, pepper crab & Bittergourd pork ribs! Reasonably priced though the place might not be very clean or nice.
Cod fish is blend & fishy. Aircon drizzles >5 times thus don't take the corner seat below it. Service is poor. Glad that I'm not going to miss the food here anymore.
The Thali Set is good. I particularly like their curd and lassi.
Nice to jump and sweat it out. For the not-very-healthy, you might want to have more intervals to rest as you might feel giddy & feel your knee aching after jumping.
Char Siew is tender but nothing to rave about. Roast meat & duck a bit dry but quite tasty. Hot & sour soup is too spicy with chilli padi while pork belly salted fish is rather oily. The usual fare
I like the hotpot (be it meat or seafood). It's tasty and the portion is generous. Root beer float is served in a huge glass. I'll be back!!
Food is cheap, salty & portion is generous but Sgreans may not like the strong PRC taste. Place is packed with PRCs & noisy. May be more suitable for PRCs as no other locals are detected.
Just had dinner. Pho beef slices is good. Prawns are fresh but I do not like the way it's cooked cos there's a funny smell. Chicken wings are ok. Avocado & Tamarind juices are good.
Fresh huge tasty lobster & chilli crab. Must try!!
Good service & nice food. However I prefer their Shanghai outlet. For whatever reason, I have headache & tummy ache after the hotpot meal. $40+ per pax.

formattedAddress: #02-04 Blk 3D River Valley Rd, Clarke Quay

tip.text: Pistachio Creme is good, so is pan-seared seabass & beef tenderloin. Foie gras is not done to my liking though the sauce is good.
Nice cha siu ramen and broth with sesame and free flow of eggs =D
Nice Mixed Platter and Kunefe dessert that's very tasty and not too sweet. Thumbs up!
The herbal chicken soup is ok but the service is so-so
